de.opendiabetes.vault.data

Class VaultDao

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.opendiabetes.vault.data.VaultDao

  • public final class VaultDao
extends java.lang.Object
    The class implements an interface to the database used. It does so by using the Database Access Objects defined in Dao.

      • getInstance

        public static VaultDao getInstance()
        Getter for the instance of the database. If the database has not been initialized by calling initializeDb() this will terminate the execution.
        Returns:
        The instance of the Vault Database Access Object, provided it has been initialized by initializeDb().

      • finalizeDb

        public static void finalizeDb()
                       throws java.io.IOException
        Closes the connection to the database and thus finalizes the Vault Database Access Object instance.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown if the connection to the database can not be closed.

      • initializeDb

        public static void initializeDb()
                         throws java.sql.SQLException
        Initializes the connection to the database and sets up the Vault Database Access Object instance.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - Thrown if the database can not be successfully initialized.

        public boolean removeDuplicates()

      • queryExerciseBetween

        public java.util.List<VaultEntry> queryExerciseBetween(java.util.Date from,
                                                       java.util.Date to)
        This method is used to query VaultEntrys which are of a given type and lie in a specified period. The types to be queried for are exercise types:
        • VaultEntryType.EXERCISE_LOW
        • VaultEntryType.EXERCISE_MID
        • VaultEntryType.EXERCISE_HIGH
        • VaultEntryType.EXERCISE_MANUAL
        Parameters:
        from - The start of the period to query entries from.
        to - The end of the period to query entries from.
        Returns:
        All VaultEntry which are of the required type and lie in the specified period.

      • queryLatestEventBefore

        public VaultEntry queryLatestEventBefore(java.util.Date timestamp,
                                         VaultEntryType type)
        This is used to query a single Event (VaultEntry before a given point in time. This is useful to determine why certain events might have happened (correlation of events).
        Parameters:
        timestamp - The point in time to get the preceding event from.
        type - The Type of VaultEntry to query for.
        Returns:
        The event of the VaultEntryType preceding the specified point in time.

      • queryAllVaultEntries

        public java.util.List<VaultEntry> queryAllVaultEntries()
        This is used to query all VaultEntrys currently store in the database.
        Returns:
        The full list of all VaultEntrys in the database.

      • queryVaultEntryById

        public VaultEntry queryVaultEntryById(long id)

      • queryVaultEntriesBetween

        public java.util.List<VaultEntry> queryVaultEntriesBetween(java.util.Date from,
                                                           java.util.Date to)
        This is used to retrieve all VaultEntrys from the database which lie in the specified period of time, no matter their type.
        Parameters:
        from - The start of the time period to query entries from.
        to - The end of the time period to query entries from.
        Returns:
        List of all VaultEntrys which lie in the specified time period.

      • queryBasalBetween

        public java.util.List<VaultEntry> queryBasalBetween(java.util.Date from,
                                                    java.util.Date to)
        This method is used to query VaultEntrys which are of a given type and lie in a specified period. The types to be queried for are basal types:
        • VaultEntryType.BASAL_MANUAL
        • VaultEntryType.BASAL_PROFILE
        • VaultEntryType.BASAL_INTERPRETER
        Parameters:
        from - The start of the period to query entries from.
        to - The end of the period to query entries from.
        Returns:
        All VaultEntry which are of the required type and lie in the specified period.
